Dynamic library version of Open-JTalk (for C and Python)

stated on 2010-06-27 by Takuya Nishimoto

Notice: This is unfinished work. See 'lib' directory.

http://ja.nishimotz.com/open-jtalk

Environment: Ubuntu Linux 9.04 / 10.04

$ sudo aptitude install autoconf libtool
$ autoreconf

== how to test shared-lib ==

$ cd /usr/local/share
$ sudo mkdir /open_jtalk
$ sudo tar xvfz /path/to/open_jtalk_dic_utf8-1.00.tar.gz
$ sudo tar xvfz /path/to/hts_voice_nitech_jp_atr503_m001-1.01.tar.gz

$ sh configure --with-charset=UTF-8
$ make
$ cd lib
$ make -f Makefile.shlib
$ export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=.
$ ./dlmain -ow _hoge.wav input.txt

